What kind of beard is this?

261
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,233
Is it true?

262
00:12:22,367 --> 00:12:25,200
- Oh, where's Grandma?
- Oh, hi, Bobby.'

263
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:27,500
She stepped out.
There's someone outside.

264
00:12:27,633 --> 00:12:29,367
I don't know who it is.

265
00:12:29,933 --> 00:12:31,100
Come in, come in

266
00:12:31,233 --> 00:12:32,600
Bobby! Bobby!

267
00:12:32,733 --> 00:12:33,767
Someone's looking for you.

268
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:34,767
Who is it, Grandma?

269
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:36,500
Come in.

270
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:41,033
- Oh.
- Enriquez...

271
00:12:47,167 --> 00:12:48,667
Hurry up, Sis!

272
00:12:55,067 --> 00:12:56,400
Sir Tonyo!

273
00:12:56,533 --> 00:12:58,100
Have some coffee first.

274
00:12:58,233 --> 00:12:59,600
Oh my Grandma, you even went out
of your way.

275
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:01,600
- Thank you very much.
- Of course.

276
00:13:01,733 --> 00:13:03,700
- Thank you.
- That's for you.

277
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:05,833
Good morning, Captain.

278
00:13:05,967 --> 00:13:08,133
- Mr. Tonyo is here.
- Hey, man.

279
00:13:08,267 --> 00:13:09,733
How are you?

280
00:13:09,867 --> 00:13:11,133
- How are you, man?
- Oh...

281
00:13:11,267 --> 00:13:12,967
I'm fine, I'm fine.

282
00:13:15,333 --> 00:13:16,667
Sir.

283
00:13:17,267 --> 00:13:18,067
Enriquez.

284
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:20,400
Thanks for bringing
the medicine here.

285
00:13:20,533 --> 00:13:22,733
You should've brought
that to the precinct.

286
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:24,300
That's nothing,

287
00:13:24,433 --> 00:13:26,367
after what you did
to me last night.

288
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:28,467
- Did something?
- Last night?

289
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:30,067
- I wish everyone had that.
- I wish everyone had that.

290
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:32,367
Sir, what did my granddaughter
do to you?

291
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:34,733
Grandma, I didn't do anything.

292
00:13:34,867 --> 00:13:37,267
Ah, no, Grandma,

293
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:39,233
it's because Bobby
took me home last night

294
00:13:39,367 --> 00:13:41,433
because I got beaten up.

295
00:13:41,567 --> 00:13:43,033
And...

296
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:45,467
she forgot this at home.

297
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:47,867
Maybe you need it,
so I brought it here on purpose.

298
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,233
Oh, the medicines.

299
00:13:49,367 --> 00:13:51,267
I need these medicines.

300
00:13:52,333 --> 00:13:54,067
Grandma...

301
00:13:55,567 --> 00:13:57,233
Sorry, Sir.

302
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:02,767
So, Enriquez, I'll go ahead.

303
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:05,000
Mar, Abdul, nice to meet you.

304
00:14:05,133 --> 00:14:08,500
Dude, come back anytime.

305
00:14:08,633 --> 00:14:10,367
Yes, Sir, even at night,

306
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:11,600
even if Bobby isn't here,

307
00:14:11,733 --> 00:14:13,067
just come visit.

308
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,600
- Yes, anytime, at night.
- Yes.

309
00:14:14,733 --> 00:14:17,033
Grandma, thank you very much
again for the coffee.

310
00:14:17,167 --> 00:14:18,767
Oh, yes, of course.

311
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:21,500
You can have coffee here
anytime.

312
00:14:21,633 --> 00:14:23,200
Okay, I'll go ahead.

313
00:14:23,333 --> 00:14:24,833
- Enriquez.
- Okay, Sir.

314
00:14:25,333 --> 00:14:26,767
Bye.

315
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:36,833
Hey! You're noisy!

316
00:14:38,433 --> 00:14:39,600
Grandma...

317
00:14:39,733 --> 00:14:40,867
Grandma, that's enough.

318
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,000
Come on, I'll bring you to work.

319
00:14:42,133 --> 00:14:43,300
You too, Captain?

320
00:14:43,433 --> 00:14:44,900
Restrain yourself.

321
00:14:47,300 --> 00:14:49,667
Sir Tonyo is fine, right?

322
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:52,167
He looks like he smells good.
Wow! Wow!

323
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:54,133
You know, that's true.

324
00:14:54,267 --> 00:14:55,567
I noticed that too.

325
00:14:55,700 --> 00:14:57,900
He looks like husband material.

326
00:14:58,033 --> 00:15:00,033
- Hey!
- Right?

327
00:15:00,167 --> 00:15:02,567
That's right!

328
00:15:02,733 --> 00:15:03,833
I'm thrilled.

329
00:15:03,967 --> 00:15:05,133
Of course.

330
00:15:05,267 --> 00:15:06,200
Of course, Grandma.

331
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:09,100
You know, my opinion
of Sir Tonyo has changed.

332
00:15:09,533 --> 00:15:13,300
I just can't imagine his life
now that he's home alone.

333
00:15:13,433 --> 00:15:16,167
Oh, my, it's really hard to lose
someone,

334
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:18,233
right?

335
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,900
Let's go.

336
00:15:32,700 --> 00:15:34,667
Are you okay, Dear?

337
00:15:39,667 --> 00:15:42,733
If only I had done something
different that day,

338
00:15:42,867 --> 00:15:45,233
I wish Godmother Dina
was still alive.

339
00:15:48,433 --> 00:15:50,933
I wish Sir Tonyo's girlfriend
was still alive.

340
00:15:51,067 --> 00:15:53,700
Oh, that's okay, Dear.

341
00:15:53,833 --> 00:15:55,333
Just hide that

342
00:15:55,467 --> 00:15:59,067
because you can use it to help
them.

343
00:16:02,333 --> 00:16:04,367
Okay, Grandma
I'll go ahead, okay?

344
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:05,900
Take care.

345
00:16:06,033 --> 00:16:07,433
- Okay, Bobby.
- Bobby, be careful, okay?

346
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:09,800
Hey, Abdul, Mars, take care of
Grandma, okay?

347
00:16:09,967 --> 00:16:11,467
- Take care, Bobby.
- We'll take care of Captain.

348
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:13,333
- You take care of Tonyo, okay?
- Take care, Dear. Take care..

349
00:16:13,467 --> 00:16:16,467
Say hi to Tonyo for us!

350
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:18,733
Work, work.

351
00:16:36,733 --> 00:16:38,200
Hey, Enriquez.

352
00:16:38,333 --> 00:16:39,900
Have you seen Lieutenant Conde?

353
00:16:40,033 --> 00:16:41,800
Huh? No!

354
00:16:41,967 --> 00:16:43,300
What are you saying?

355
00:16:43,433 --> 00:16:44,567
You know, I just got here.

356
00:16:44,700 --> 00:16:48,000
It's impossible for the
two of us to meet.

357
00:16:48,133 --> 00:16:51,000
I just got here, you,
what are you saying?

358
00:16:52,967 --> 00:16:53,967
What happened there?

359
00:16:54,100 --> 00:16:56,467
I was just asking.

360
00:17:17,833 --> 00:17:19,400
Enriquez.

361
00:17:20,633 --> 00:17:22,067
Are you looking for something?

362
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:24,567
Looking for something?
Oh, nothing, nothing.

363
00:17:25,033 --> 00:17:26,567
Chief, that's just an excuse.

364
00:17:26,700 --> 00:17:28,367
She's just looking for me.

365
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:29,900
Enriquez, not now.

366
00:17:30,033 --> 00:17:32,333
Let's work first, okay?

367
00:17:55,100 --> 00:17:57,100
Why not?

368
00:18:05,133 --> 00:18:07,267
I can shoot that
for three points.

369
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:14,667
Oh, oh...

370
00:18:17,233 --> 00:18:18,333
Sir...

371
00:18:18,467 --> 00:18:19,533
Sir, sorry, Sir.

372
00:18:19,667 --> 00:18:21,100
Sorry.

373
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:23,867
It's because I am doing...

374
00:18:24,433 --> 00:18:25,567
I'm going to throw it away.

375
00:18:25,700 --> 00:18:26,600
I'm looking for a trash can.

376
00:18:26,733 --> 00:18:28,300
When I tried to shoot you,
you were there.

377
00:18:28,433 --> 00:18:29,600
So it's my fault?

378
00:18:29,733 --> 00:18:31,333
Oh, no! No, no, Sir.

379
00:18:31,467 --> 00:18:33,800
Sorry, sorry.

380
00:18:39,900 --> 00:18:42,200
<i> Your body is big, Sir.</i>

381
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:46,333
Sorry again, Sir.

382
00:18:57,700 --> 00:18:59,400
Enriquez...

383
00:19:01,100 --> 00:19:03,567
Do you want to talk about what
happened last night?

384
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:06,600
What's that, Sir?

385
00:19:06,733 --> 00:19:08,333
Nothing happened, Sir.

386
00:19:08,467 --> 00:19:09,767
Are you sure?

387
00:19:09,900 --> 00:19:11,633
Yes, Sir, nothing!

388
00:19:12,033 --> 00:19:13,000
I'm sure.

389
00:19:13,133 --> 00:19:16,200
No, are you sure you don't want
to talk about it?

390
00:19:16,333 --> 00:19:17,867
Oh, yes, Sir.

391
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:19,133
I don't want to talk about it.

392
00:19:19,267 --> 00:19:22,133
Oh, no, we have nothing
to talk about.

393
00:19:24,367 --> 00:19:25,767
Okay.

394
00:19:35,933 --> 00:19:38,600
Three points, there you go
with three points.

395
00:19:41,233 --> 00:19:43,533
You know, it's really my fault

396
00:19:43,667 --> 00:19:45,367
because I left you.

397
00:19:45,500 --> 00:19:48,733
When you're left behind,
you're out of control.

398
00:19:48,867 --> 00:19:50,933
It's a good thing you got home.

399
00:19:51,367 --> 00:19:52,467
Wait a minute.

400
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:54,500
How did you get home last night?

401
00:19:55,133 --> 00:19:57,833
Enriquez, can you help me?

402
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:00,267
Chief asked me to do something.

403
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:02,800
Come on. What do you need?

404
00:20:06,700 --> 00:20:07,967
Bok...

405
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:10,167
how are you and Enriquez?

406
00:20:10,300 --> 00:20:11,900
We're fine.

407
00:20:12,033 --> 00:20:15,567
Oh, Chief doesn't like fights
like that.

408
00:20:17,733 --> 00:20:19,500
But you know, I think

409
00:20:19,633 --> 00:20:22,933
she's just fighting you
to get closer to me.

410
00:20:23,067 --> 00:20:24,267
That's her style.

411
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:26,567
Guys, the Chief's calling us.

412
00:20:32,767 --> 00:20:35,267
The case is not moving forward

413
00:20:35,433 --> 00:20:37,367
and we have no new leads.

414
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:40,500
So let's take a different turn.

415
00:20:42,300 --> 00:20:45,033
Sorry, Sir, I'm late.
I just read the message.

416
00:20:50,267 --> 00:20:52,900
We're focusing too much on Sonny

417
00:20:53,033 --> 00:20:55,400
and who knocked him down.

418
00:20:55,533 --> 00:20:58,633
Better yet, let's go after

419
00:20:58,767 --> 00:21:00,433
those who might have a motive

420
00:21:00,567 --> 00:21:03,133
for kidnapping
the Mayor's daughter.

421
00:21:03,267 --> 00:21:04,200
Keep in mind.

422
00:21:04,333 --> 00:21:06,667
If we solve this case,

423
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:09,000
maybe we can solve
the other cases too.

424
00:21:09,167 --> 00:21:10,333
Is that clear?

425
00:21:10,467 --> 00:21:12,533
Sir, yes, Sir.

426
00:21:12,667 --> 00:21:14,267
You're all dismissed.

427
00:21:18,167 --> 00:21:20,933
Enriquez, stay behind.

428
00:21:28,833 --> 00:21:31,733
I saw your altercation with
Conde yesterday.

429
00:21:32,633 --> 00:21:34,300
Oh, that's nothing, Sir.

430
00:21:34,433 --> 00:21:38,067
Make sure you two don't do
anything stupid today

431
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:40,000
because the mayor
will award you.

432
00:21:40,133 --> 00:21:43,300
You, Conde, Noble, and Dizon.

433
00:21:43,467 --> 00:21:45,233
Ah, award Sir?

434
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:46,267
What for?

435
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:48,333
Because you saved
the Mayor's daughter.

436
00:21:48,467 --> 00:21:51,100
But Noble and Dizon will follow.

437
00:21:51,233 --> 00:21:54,900
Conde and you can go ahead to
Barangay Sta. Fe.

438
00:21:55,033 --> 00:21:55,867
What?

439
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,967
You can go, Enriquez.

440
00:22:06,433 --> 00:22:10,267
Just when you're avoiding him.

441
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:13,300
Why do we have to go together?

442
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:14,700
Noble!

443
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:16,133
Ma'am?

444
00:22:16,633 --> 00:22:19,567
Where are you going?
Aren't you going with Tonyo?

445
00:22:19,700 --> 00:22:20,800
Mmm, no, no, Ma'am.

446
00:22:20,933 --> 00:22:22,300
We have something else
to take care of.

447
00:22:22,433 --> 00:22:23,967
Maybe we'll just follow.

448
00:22:25,233 --> 00:22:26,033
Okay.

449
00:22:26,700 --> 00:22:27,900
Okay, Ma'am.

450
00:22:28,033 --> 00:22:29,267
Hurry up, huh?

451
00:22:36,800 --> 00:22:38,667
Enriquez, let's go.

452
00:22:38,800 --> 00:22:41,033
Sir, ah, where are we going?

453
00:22:41,167 --> 00:22:43,100
We're going to the awarding,
right?

454
00:22:43,233 --> 00:22:44,700
Ah, yes.

455
00:22:46,100 --> 00:22:49,567
Conde, can I go with you?

456
00:22:49,733 --> 00:22:51,767
Do you want to go with us,
Sir? Okay, Sir.

457
00:22:51,900 --> 00:22:53,533
Enriquez, calm down.

458
00:22:53,667 --> 00:22:54,967
You're too obvious.

459
00:22:55,700 --> 00:22:58,367
I thought you and Robles had an
assignment too.

460
00:22:58,500 --> 00:23:00,633
Robles can handle that.

461
00:23:00,767 --> 00:23:02,300
What? I'll go with you.

462
00:23:02,433 --> 00:23:03,733
Yes, Sir, that's okay.

463
00:23:03,867 --> 00:23:06,000
The more, the merrier.

464
00:23:06,467 --> 00:23:08,933
Enriquez, Enriquez,
don't be so aggressive.

465
00:23:09,067 --> 00:23:10,400
I'm getting turned off.

466
00:23:10,533 --> 00:23:13,333
Garcia, you can't join.

467
00:23:13,467 --> 00:23:17,333
If you want to catch up with the
fiesta, finish your work here.

468
00:23:18,233 --> 00:23:20,533
Conde, go ahead, leave.

469
00:23:20,667 --> 00:23:21,533
Yes, Sir.

470
00:23:23,733 --> 00:23:25,800
Well, Enriquez, I'm sorry,

471
00:23:25,933 --> 00:23:29,700
but I can't fulfill your dream
of being with me.

472
00:23:30,900 --> 00:23:31,867
Sorry.

473
00:23:38,133 --> 00:23:40,500
Enriquez, come on.

474
00:23:40,633 --> 00:23:41,433
Let's go.

475
00:23:41,733 --> 00:23:42,867
Oh, Roman?

476
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:45,333
are you going to tell me
something about the police?

477
00:23:45,467 --> 00:23:47,333
There's a newbie at Station 12.

478
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:49,567
<i> You're the one suspected</i>

479
00:23:49,700 --> 00:23:51,967
<i>of being behind all the chaos
that's been going on.</i>

480
00:23:52,100 --> 00:23:53,033
Who is that?

481
00:23:53,167 --> 00:23:55,000
Sergeant Enriquez.

482
00:23:55,167 --> 00:23:57,300
Sergeant Enriquez...

483
00:23:57,433 --> 00:23:59,667
I think I know who you're
talking about.

484
00:24:00,133 --> 00:24:02,067
<i>- Sergeant Enriquez...
- Boss?</i>

485
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:04,700
<i>what was the result of your
investigation?</i>

486
00:24:04,833 --> 00:24:08,233
<i>Your masks were
used in the robbery.</i>

487
00:24:08,367 --> 00:24:11,933
<i>That means the same group robbed
the museum</i>

488
00:24:12,067 --> 00:24:14,767
<i>and the same group robbed
the San Isidro Rural Bank.</i>

489
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:16,033
<i> Good morning, Boss.</i>

490
00:24:16,167 --> 00:24:18,100
<i> Oh, good morning too.</i>

491
00:24:18,233 --> 00:24:21,133
<i> I thought you were here</i>

492
00:24:21,267 --> 00:24:22,533
<i>because you wanted to
investigate me.</i>

493
00:24:22,667 --> 00:24:24,300
<i> Investigate?</i>

494
00:24:24,433 --> 00:24:27,033
Roman, make sure

495
00:24:27,167 --> 00:24:30,100
they don't find any holes in me.

496
00:24:30,267 --> 00:24:34,200
I want the police to take their
eyes off me,

497
00:24:34,333 --> 00:24:37,233
especially Sergeant Enriquez.

498
00:24:38,300 --> 00:24:39,967
Consider it done, Boss.

499
00:24:50,100 --> 00:24:51,433
<i> Here it is.</i>

500
00:24:51,567 --> 00:24:53,133
<i>Please check if it went through.</i>

501
00:24:53,267 --> 00:24:54,733
<i> Okay, we got it.</i>

502
00:24:54,867 --> 00:24:58,533
<i>Next time, tell your boyfriend
not to get drunk here.</i>

503
00:25:02,533 --> 00:25:05,200
Enriquez, are you okay?

504
00:25:06,367 --> 00:25:08,100
You seem to be deep in thought,
ha.

505
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:10,500
Oh...

506
00:25:10,633 --> 00:25:12,533
I was just thinking about last
night, Sir...

507
00:25:13,900 --> 00:25:15,500
Last night?

508
00:25:17,300 --> 00:25:21,967
No, because, Sir you owe me,
five thousand.

509
00:25:22,100 --> 00:25:23,267
Five thousand?

510
00:25:23,400 --> 00:25:28,067
Yes, Sir, the ones that were
broken at the convenience store.

511
00:25:28,533 --> 00:25:29,900
Oh my,

512
00:25:30,033 --> 00:25:31,200
you didn't even negotiate?

513
00:25:31,333 --> 00:25:32,800
Five thousand, really?

514
00:25:33,467 --> 00:25:35,133
Yes, five thousand.

515
00:25:37,367 --> 00:25:38,767
I was wondering

516
00:25:38,900 --> 00:25:40,967
what you did to me.

517
00:25:41,900 --> 00:25:45,467
Hey, Sir, I'm not like that.

518
00:25:46,167 --> 00:25:48,333
Hey, why do you think like that?

519
00:25:48,467 --> 00:25:49,233
Calm down.

520
00:25:49,367 --> 00:25:50,800
Just kidding! What's with you?

521
00:25:50,933 --> 00:25:52,733
Can't you take a joke?

522
00:25:53,133 --> 00:25:54,600
Let's go.

523
00:25:57,467 --> 00:25:58,867
Enriquez.

524
00:26:01,367 --> 00:26:03,200
What's that? What's that?

525
00:26:03,333 --> 00:26:06,600
Sir, hey, you're too much.

526
00:26:06,733 --> 00:26:08,733
- What's that?
- Your seatbelt.

527
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:11,233
Well, you have to make it clear
what you're saying.

528
00:26:11,367 --> 00:26:12,700
You were doing this...

529
00:26:12,833 --> 00:26:14,400
I thought it was something.

530
00:26:14,533 --> 00:26:15,800
You're so grumpy.

531
00:26:15,933 --> 00:26:17,133
Let's go.

532
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:25,500
Are you Bullet?

533
00:26:28,933 --> 00:26:30,100
Yes.

534
00:26:37,100 --> 00:26:38,567
Here's the target.

535
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:42,733
Hey.

536
00:26:42,900 --> 00:26:44,700
You listen to me.

537
00:26:45,867 --> 00:26:49,300
This job is very important,
okay?

538
00:26:49,767 --> 00:26:50,667
So you...

539
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:52,067
Hey.

540
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:53,867
You listen.

541
00:26:54,733 --> 00:26:56,933
I never miss.

542
00:27:00,467 --> 00:27:01,367
- Hello?
- Hello, Chief?

543
00:27:01,500 --> 00:27:02,233
I need backup.

544
00:27:02,367 --> 00:27:03,567
I followed some kidnappers.

545
00:27:03,700 --> 00:27:05,300
They kidnapped someone in
Calabari Townsquare

546
00:27:05,433 --> 00:27:06,567
and it looks like I'm already in
their hideout.

547
00:27:06,700 --> 00:27:08,167
We were kidnapped.

548
00:27:10,633 --> 00:27:11,700
Have you seen that biker video,

549
00:27:11,833 --> 00:27:13,067
the one where the riders were
being shot?

550
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:14,167
We should have been in there.

551
00:27:14,300 --> 00:27:15,167
We failed to go there

552
00:27:15,300 --> 00:27:16,333
because the Mayor ordered us to
roast a pig.

553
00:27:16,500 --> 00:27:17,800
Oh my.

554
00:27:18,367 --> 00:27:19,600
Come on, Mar!

555
00:27:19,733 --> 00:27:20,933
What's with his face...

556
00:27:21,067 --> 00:27:21,867
Oh, he looks like

557
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:24,367
our mysterious guy, Bro.

558
00:27:24,500 --> 00:27:26,000
Is that him?
